cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Protocol Performance Evaluation Dataset
abstract: This dataset contains results from an experiment designed to evaluate the
  performance characteristics of various QUIC protocol implementations under different
  bandwidth constraints. The methodology involved establishing a server and client
  environment across two nodes (tartu and tallinn) using automated scripts for system
  configuration, time synchronization, and package installation. Measurements focused
  on goodput performance, captured through server energy monitoring and client-side
  execution timing, alongside associated metrics like mean and standard deviation.
  The data includes generated plots visualizing goodput variations and tabular results
  documenting the raw experiment output, facilitating detailed analysis of QUIC protocol
  behavior.
